The paper discusses the Neural Arithmetic Logic Unit (NALU), which is a neural network layer used for learning arithmetic operations. This falls under the category of machine learning and neural networks, which is covered by cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the NALU's performance, which involves measuring its ability to learn arithmetic extrapolation. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence, which is covered by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions using the NALU for computer vision and natural language processing tasks, which fall under the categories of computer vision (cs.CV) and computational linguistics (cs.CL), respectively.
